data.title: Arizona Postal History - Tucson
data.text: Hand cancellation: "TUCSON, A.T. MAR 23 [1867]". [TPC] [This is the earliest known Tucson, Arizona Territory, postmark. I donated it to the Postal History Foundation in Tucson - Click here to read a newspaper article about this donation] This cacheted cover is for National Aviation Day and commemorates the 30th anniversary of flight. Hand cancellation: "Tucson, Ariz. DEC 16 1933 ( 1 )". This cacheted cover is for the first jet airmail flight AM-4 from Tucson to Chicago. Machine cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. SEP 1 1960". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Project Mercury 4 cents postage stamp. Hand cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. FEB 20 1962". This cacheted cover commemorates President John F. Kennedy and is also for the first day of issue of the John F. Kennedy 5 cents postage stamp. Machine cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. 1B MAY 29 1964". This cacheted cover salutes the opening of the Sabino Canyon Visitor Center. Machine pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. JUN 13 1964 | Remember Only you can PREVENT FOREST FIRES |". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the U. S. Postal Service 8 cents postage stamp. Machine cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. JUL 1 1971". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the U. S. Postal Service 8 cents postage stamp. Machine pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. JUL 1 1971 | SUPPORT YOUR MENTAL HEALTH ASSOCIATION |". This cacheted cover is for the 1969 Spring Meeting of the American Philatelic Society. Hand cancellation: "AMERICAN PHILATELIC SOC. EX. STA., TUCSON, AZ APR 18 1969". This cacheted cover is for the 1969 Spring Meeting of the American Philatelic Society. Hand cancellation: "AMERICAN PHILATELIC SOC. EX. STA., TUCSON, AZ APR 19 1969". This cacheted cover is for the 1969 Spring Meeting of the American Philatelic Society. Hand cancellation: "AMERICAN PHILATELIC SOC. EX. STA., TUCSON, AZ APR 20 1969". Hand cancellation on back: "ANNEX STA., TUCSON, ARIZ. MAR 7 1959". Has "REGISTERED NO." and "RETURN RECEIPT REQUESTED" auxiliary markings on front. This cacheted cover commemorates President John F. Kennedy and is also for the first day of issue of the John F. Kennedy 5 cents postage stamp. Hand cancellation: "ANNEX STA., TUCSON, ARIZ. MY 29 1964". This cacheted cover is for the combined ARIPEX, NORDIA and APS 2001 exhibition. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "ARIPEX STATION, TUCSON, ARIZONA 85701 JAN 19 2001 | PHILATELIC STAMPEDE FUN IN THE SUN IN TUCSON, ARIZONA WITH ARIPEX, NORDIA AND THE APS 2001 |". This cacheted cover commemorates the Anza Expedition of 1775-1776 and salutes the ARIPEX 1976 show. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "ARIPEX '76 STA., TUCSON, AZ 85705 JAN 24 1976 | The ANZA EXPEDITION 1775-1776 Sonora, Mexico, Arizona & California BICENTENNIAL COMMEMORATION |". This cacheted cover is for the 2005 ARIPEX exhibition. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "ARIPEX '05 STA., TUCSON, AZ 85701 JAN 23 2005 | TUCSON, ARIZONA SOUTHERN PACIFIC RAILROAD - 1880-2005 - 125 YEARS, FIRST TRAIN TO TUCSON TRAIN 3 |". This cacheted cover commemorates Tucson having served as the capital of the Arizona Territory 1867-1877. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "ARIZONA CAPITAL STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 NOVEMBER 1, 2017 | TUCSON 150 YEARS 1867-2017 |". This cacheted cover commemorates the 100th anniversary of Arizona statehood. It is also for the first day of issue of the 2012 Arizona centennial forever postage stamp. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "ARIZONA CENTENNIAL STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 FEB14, 2012 | 1912 2012 |". This cacheted cover commemorates the Civil War centennial in Arizona. It is also for the first day of issue of the Arizona Statehood 4 cents postage stamp. Special commemorative hand slogan cancellation: "ARIZONA PIONEERS' HISTORICAL SOCIETY UNIT, TUCSON, ARIZ. FEB 14 1962 | STATEHOOD GOLDEN JUBILEE 1912 - 1962 |". This cacheted cover commemorates the establishment of the Territory of Arizona in 1863. Special hand pictorial cancellation: "ARIZONA TERRITORIAL STATION, Tucson, AZ 85719 February 24, 2013". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Elvis 29 cents postage stamp. Hand cancellation: "CONTRACT STA. 53, TUCSON, AZ USPO JAN 8 1993". This cacheted cover is for the first day of operation of the Postal History Foundation. Hand cancellation: "CONTRACT STA. 61, TUCSON, AZ USPO SEP 21 1992". This cacheted cover is for the Desert Con V Science Fiction Conference. It has a special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "DESERT CON STA., TUCSON, AZ 85720 FEB 18 1977 | Desert Con V FEB. 17-20 |". This cacheted cover is for the Watershed Exposition in Tucson. It has a special hand slogan cancellation: "DESERT MUSEUM STA., TUCSON, ARIZ. APRIL 23 1960 | WATERSHED EXPOSITION SPECIAL OBSERVANCE |". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Gadsden Purchase 3 cents postage stamp. Special machine slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. DEC 30 1953 | FIRST DAY OF ISSUE |". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Forest Conservation 4 cents postage stamp. Special machine pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, ARIZ. OCT 27 1958 | FIRST DAY OF ISSUE |". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Desert Plants series of 20 cents postage stamps. Special machine slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, AZ 85726 DEC 11 1981 | FIRST DAY OF ISSUE |". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the 1920s Tow Truck 8.5 cents postage stamp. Special machine slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, AZ 85726 JAN 24 1987 | FIRST DAY OF ISSUE |". This cacheted cover commemorates the 200th anniversary of the birth of President Lincoln. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "LINCOLN STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 FEBRUARY 9 2009 BICENTENNIAL OF ABRAHAM LINCOLN'S BIRTHDAY ". This cacheted cover commemorates the 40th anniversary of the sinking of the U. S. S. Arizona, December 7, 1941. Hand cancellation: "( MAILER'S POSTMARK PERMIT # 1 ) TUCSON, AZ 85710 DEC 7 1981". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the San Xavier del Bac Mission 8 cents postage stamp. Hand cancellation: "MAIN OFFICE, TUCSON, AZ OCT 29 1971". This cacheted cover is for the dedication of the Tucson Community Center. Hand cancellation: "MAIN OFFICE, TUCSON, AZ NOV 6 1971". This cacheted cover commemorates the sinking of the U. S. S. Arizona in 1941. Hand cancellation: "MAIN OFFICE, TUCSON, AZ DEC 7 1971". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Postal Service People series of 10 different 8 cents postage stamps. Hand cancellation: "MAIN OFFICE, TUCSON, AZ APR 30 1973". This cacheted cover is for the inaugural United Airlines airmail flight from Tucson to New York. Hand cancellation: "MAIN OFFICE, TUCSON, AZ USPO DEC 18 1980". This cacheted cover is for the inaugural Western Airlines airmail flight from Tucson to Phoenix. Hand cancellation: "MAIN OFFICE, TUCSON, AZ USPO DEC 1 1982". This cacheted cover is for the inaugural run of the Tucson modern streetcar. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "MODERN STREETCAR STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 JULY 25, 2014 | TRIP 1 |". Hand cancellation: "OLD PUEBLO STA., TUCSON, ARIZ. JUL 7 1952 ( 1 )". Has "Received without contents at Old Pueblo Station .... 6th & Alameda" auxiliary marking. This cacheted cover commemorates Tucson's 243rd birthday and is also for the first day of issue of the special Tucson 1775-2018 50 cents postage stamp. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "OLD PUEBLO STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 AUGUST 20 2018 | 243 YEARS TUCSON BIRTHDAY 1775-2018 |". This cacheted cover is for the dedication of the Old Pueblo Philatelic Center. Hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "PHILATELIC CENTER, Tucson, AZ 85726 JAN 27 1983 | "The Old Pueblo" |". This cacheted cover is for the first day of issue of the Celebrate the Century Grand Canyon 32 cents postage stamp. Special hand pictorial cancellation: "POSTAL HISTORY STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 FEBRUARY 3 1998". This cacheted cover features the 33rd annual Tucson Gem & Mineral Show. It has a special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "RED CLOUD STA., TUCSON, AZ 85701 FEB 14 1987 | Tucson Gem & Mineral Show * Feb 12-15 1987 |". Hand cancellation on back: "REGISTERED, TUCSON, ARIZ. SEP 3 1937". Has "REGISTERED NO." auxiliary marking on front. This cacheted cover is for the 1992 Tucson Stamp Club Park Mall Show. Hand cancellation: "STA. 28, TUCSON, AZ USPO OCT 3 1992". The cover also has a postage stamp and hand pictorial cancellation from the Tucson Stamp Club Local Post. Hand cancellation on front & back: "STA. NO. 49, TUCSON, AZ USPO MAY 17 1983". This cacheted cover commemorates the 100th anniversary of the University of Arizona. It has a special hand slogan cancellation: "STUDENT UNION STA., TUCSON, AZ 85721 March 12 1985 | The University of Arizona 1885 1985 One Hundred Years A Proud Beginning |". This cacheted cover features the Total Solar Eclipse of August 21, 2017. Hand cancellation: "SUN STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85719 USPS AUG 21 2017". This cacheted cover features Tohono Chul Park. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "Tohono Chul Park Station, Tucson, AZ 85704 June 29, 2007 ( "Queen of the Night" Peniocereus greggii )". This cacheted cover commemorates the Old Pueblo Trolley. Special hand pictorial cancellation: "TROLLEY STATION, TUCSON, ARIZONA 85726 APR 17 1993 ( RPO )". These cacheted covers feature the Tucson International Airport. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "Tucson Airport Station, Tucson, AZ 85768 October 24 1985 | DEDICATION - TUCSON INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT |". This cacheted cover commemorates the 50th anniversary of the Tucson Airport. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON AIRPORT STATION, TUCSON, ARIZONA 85706 OCT 14 1998 | CELEBRATING 50 YEARS 1948-1998 | ". This cacheted cover celebrates "Rudolph the Red-Nosed Reindeer". Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, AZ STATION 85719 DEC 2, 2014 ( RUDOLPH THE RED-NOSED REINDEER )". This cacheted cover features "A Charlie Brown Christmas". Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, AZ STATION 85719 OCT 2, 2015 | A CHARLIE BROWN CHRISTMAS |". This cacheted cover commemorates the 50th anniversary of the first manned moon landing. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, AZ STATION 85719 JUL 20 2019 | 1969: FIRST MOON LANDING |". This cacheted cover salutes the Droids of Star Wars. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON, AZ STATION 85757 MAY 5 2021 | STAR WARS DROIDS |". This cacheted cover is for the 16th annual Tucson Balloon Festival. Special hand pictorial cancellation: "TUCSON BALLOON FESTIVAL STATION, TUCSON, ARIZONA 85704 FEBRUARY 18 & 19, 1989". This cacheted cover commemorates the 60th anniversary of the Tucson Airport Authority. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "Tucson International Airport Station, Anniverary, Tucson, AZ 85756 October 11 2008". This cacheted cover is for the 2000 Touchstone Energy Tucson Open. It has a special hand pictorial cancellation: "TUCSON OPEN STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85742 FEB 23-27 2000". This cacheted cover features the Tucson Padres Baseball Team. Special hand pictorial cancellation: "TUCSON PADRES STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85713 AUG 25, 2012". This cacheted cover features the Tucson Stamp Club. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUCSON STAMP CLUB SHOW STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85711 OCT 10 1987 ( ARIZONA Federation of Stamp Clubs ) ( Tucson Stamp Club Founded in 1883 ) ". This cacheted cover is for the Tucson Bicentennial. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUPEX EXHIBITION STA., TUCSON, AZ. 85719 AUG 20 1975 | TUCSON 1775 - 1975 BICENTENNIAL |". This cacheted cover features the dedication of the Western Postal History Museum. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUPEX EXHIBITION STA., TUCSON, AZ. 85719 NOV 13 1978 | DEDICATION WESTERN POSTAL HISTORY MUSEUM |". This cacheted cover features the support of athletics and TUPEX. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "TUPEX EXHIBITION STA., TUCSON, AZ. 85701 Jan. 23 1981 | SUPPORT ATHLETICS |". Hand cancellation on back: "UNIVERSITY STA., TUCSON, ARIZ. FEB 4 1949". Has "REGISTERED NO." and "Return Receipt Requested" auxiliary markings on front. This cacheted cover honors the University of Arizona Softball -- 1997 National Champions. Special hand pictorial & slogan cancellation: "WILDCAT STATION, TUCSON, AZ 85721 MAY 26 1997 | SOFTBALL NATIONAL CHAMPIONS |".
